Class ImportMigrationContextImpl

    public class ImportMigrationContextImpl
extends MigrationContextImpl<MigrationReport>
implements ImportMigrationContext
    The import migration context keeps track of exported migration entries for a given migratable while processing an import migration operation.

    • Method Detail

      • getSystemPropertyReferencedEntry

        public Optional<ImportMigrationEntry> getSystemPropertyReferencedEntry(String name)
        Description copied from interface: ImportMigrationContext
        Retrieves a migration entry referenced from a given system property that was exported by the corresponding migratable.

        The entry returned would be an entry representing the file that was referenced by the specified system property value on the exported system. For example:

        If system properties defined the following mapping: javax.net.ssl.keyStore=etc/keystores/serverKeystore.jks

        then the following code: 

             final Optional<ImportMigrationEntry> entry
         = context.getSystemPropertyReferenceEntry("javax.net.ssl.keyStore");

        would return an entry representing the exported file etc/keystores/serverKeystore.jks allowing the migratable a chance to restore it in its original location and verifying that the system property is still defined with the same value after the import operation has completed.

        Specified by:
        getSystemPropertyReferencedEntry in interface ImportMigrationContext
        Parameters:
        name - the name of the system property referencing a migration entry to retrieve
        Returns:
        the corresponding migration entry or empty if it was not migrated by the corresponding migratable

      • getEntry

        public ImportMigrationEntry getEntry(Path path)
        Description copied from interface: ImportMigrationContext
        Retrieves a migration entry that was exported by the corresponding migratable with the given path.

        A "fake" entry will still be returned if the requested path was not exported. Errors will be recorded when storing the file later using one of the restore() methods or an exception will be thrown out when attempting to retrieve the corresponding input stream.

        Specified by:
        getEntry in interface ImportMigrationContext
        Parameters:
        path - the path of the file that was exported (must be relative to ${ddf.home} to match an exported entry otherwise an error or a warning will be recorded later when an attempt is made to restored to returned migration entry)
        Returns:
        the corresponding migration entry
